    "content_hash": "d868cfdafa3392ad",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "A little about us\n\n - Redefining graphic design: Kittl is transforming how creators work with an intuitive platform that stands as a modern, competitive alternative to traditional design tools: Build the new Adobe of tomorrow\n\n - Rapid growth: Millions of users within just two years of launch\n\n - Diverse team: 120+ team members representing 30+ different countries\n\n - Truly product-led company: Engineers, Product managers and designers are at the core of Kittl - shaping an engineering driven working culture\n\n - Strong funding: Raised over $45M from world-renowned investors who have also backed companies like Slack, Dropbox, and Figma\n\nLearn more: www.kittl.com/career http://www.kittl.com/career\n\nYour role at Kittl\n\nAs a Senior Performance Marketing Manager at Kittl, you will take full ownership of our paid acquisition stack with a critical mandate to revitalize our Paid Search performance. You will operate as a high-impact individual contributor, managing six-figure monthly budgets to drive efficient subscription growth.\n\nWhile maintaining our success on Social, your primary focus will be deep-diving into Google Ads data to restructure campaigns and unlock scalability. You will champion a culture of high-velocity creative testing, partnering with design teams to feed the algorithms with high-converting assets. Ultimately, you are the architect of our paid growth engine, balancing aggressive scaling with strict CPA and ROI targets.\n\nWhat you'll do\n\n - Revitalize \u0026 scale paid search: Take end-to-end ownership of Google Ads (Search, PMax, YouTube, Display), deeply analyzing and restructuring accounts to improve performance and drive scalable growth\n\n - Manage multi-channel strategy: Oversee and optimize six-figure monthly budgets across Google and Meta, ensuring efficient capital allocation to maximize blended ROI\n\n - High-velocity experimentation: Own the experimentation roadmap, executing rigorous A/B tests on ad copy, creative assets, and landing pages to constantly improve CVR and lower CPAs\n\n - Deep data analysis: Dive deep into large datasets to uncover granular insights, moving beyond surface-level metrics to optimize for LTV, CAC, and incrementality.\n\n - Creative strategy feedback: Partner closely with the Creative team to guide the development of high-performing assets, translating data insights into clear creative briefs for both static and video ads\n\n - Build automated workflows: Leverage AI tools and scripts to automate routine bidding and optimization tasks, allowing you to focus on strategy, creative testing, and finding the next growth lever\n\nWhat you’ll need\n\n - Proven paid search expertise: 4+ years of hands-on experience in Performance Marketing with a mastery of Google Ads (Search, YouTube, Display); Paid Social experience is a big plus\n\n - Budget scaling experience: A demonstrable track record of managing and scaling ad accounts with 6-figure monthly budgets, proving you can increase spend without sacrificing efficiency\n\n - Subscription growth background: Experience driving acquisition for a subscription-led business, with a strong command of unit economics like LTV \u0026 CAC\n\n - Analytical \u0026 technical depth: A deeply analytical mindset with proficiency in handling complex datasets, and a good understanding of attribution models and tracking to make evidence-based decisions\n\n - Advanced testing mindset: While proficient in standard A/B testing, you prioritize incrementality and lift analysis, looking beyond basic platform metrics to understand the true causal impact of your spend on business growth\n\n - Hunger \u0026 autonomy: You are a self-starter who thrives as an individual contributor, possessing an \"owner\" mentality to navigate ambiguity and aggressively chase performance targets\n\nInterview process\n\n - Recruiter interview (30 min)\n\n - Interview with Growth Marketing Lead (30 min)\n\n - Take-home assignment\n\n - Interview with Head of Growth \u0026 Growth Marketing Lead (60 min)\n\n - Bar raiser interview with Chief of Staff, right hand to CEO (45 min)\n\nWe are looking for someone\n\n - Exceptionally driven to drive impact and challenge the status quo\n\n - Who takes extreme ownership \u0026 gets things done\n\n - Who goes above and beyond in their role\n\n - Who is deeply passionate about what they do\n\nBenefits\n\n - Maximise your impact: No matter if you’re leading a team or you stand out by your domain expertise - all we care about is supporting you to maximise your own impact\n\n - Hackathons: Our quarterly hackathons provide an environment to experiment with new concepts, push boundaries, and potentially deliver the next big thing.\n\n - Kittl Week: Each year, our global team gathers together for a whole week, to work, celebrate, get inspired, and have fun\n\n - Flexible working hours: Our core hours are 11am–5pm CET, leaving the rest of your schedule flexible to fit your style\n\n - Remote work: Work up to 50 days (10 weeks) fully remote per year from anywhere in the world, as long as you maintain our core hours\n\n - Learning \u0026 development: Our L\u0026D budget supports your professional growth\n\n - Mobility benefit: We fully cover your monthly BVG public transport ticket\n\n - Health and fitness: Urban Sports Club membership discount\n\n - Vacation: Up to 30 vacation days per year\n\n#li-hybrid\n\n🌈 At Kittl, we embrace diversity and value every team member's unique background, identity, and experience. We're all about respect, honesty, and inclusivity. Together, we create a safe and supportive work environment where everyone thrives. Join us on this exciting journey of making our company and product even better!",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
